# Role: QA Engineer

## Test levels
- **Unit** — pytest, each service function isolated (mock OpenRouter with `pytest-httpx`)
- **Integration** — real DB (PostgreSQL in Docker), Alembic migrations applied
- **E2E** — Playwright, critical user paths only

## Test cases (P0 — must pass before demo)
| ID | Scenario |
|----|----------|
| TC-01 | Create protocol with phase=II, drug=BCD-100 → 9 sections generated |
| TC-02 | Edit title → new version created → diff shows change |
| TC-03 | `/check` returns compliance_score ≥ 0 and typed issues array |
| TC-04 | Export DOCX — file downloads, headings are H1/H2/H3 |
| TC-05 | Export contains watermark `"FOR DEMONSTRATION PURPOSES ONLY — SYNTHETIC DATA"` |
| TC-06 | `/health` returns `{"status":"ok","db":"connected"}` |

## Definition of Done
- All P0 test cases pass
- No `500` responses on valid inputs
- Frontend form validation blocks bad data (phase not in I/II/III, empty title)
- Deviation from `docs/functional-requirements.md` ≤ **15%** for standard features
- Deviation from `docs/functional-requirements.md` ≤ **25%** for AI generator behaviour

## Deviation measurement (NFR-06)
Count the total number of FR items per area. Count missing/broken items. Ratio must stay within limits.

| Scope | Max allowed deviation | Example violations |
|-------|----------------------|--------------------|
| Standard functions (forms, export, versioning) | 15% | Missing field in form, export without metadata |
| AI generator (sections, check, score) | 25% | Section missing from output, no compliance_score in /check response |

Deviations that are **not counted**: cosmetic UI differences, added conveniences that don't conflict with FR.

## Synthetic demo data
Use **BCD-100** (anti-PD-1, Phase II, oncology) and **BCD-089** (IL-17, Phase III, rheumatology) only — never real patient data.

## Checkpoints
- [ ] TC-01 through TC-06 pass
- [ ] Regression checklist run before demo
